=Description=

Juliana Oliveira:

"Source Temple is a place that you can find inside your imagination. It's located in Cunha, the countryside of São Paulo. We are approximately 40 people, from different countries, ages and cultures, working on ourselves to bring about a meeting point that is universal. We recognize that each problem comes from only a break in communication that is inside each one of us and that this break can be restored if transcended.
     
'''The core of the community is relationship and forgiveness, both with each other and ultimately with our source, which you could call universe, god or just our true essence. Source Temple could be denominated as a sacred cooperative community''' and also, as a bright model of society where the demonstration of each participant is consistenly Cooperation + Tolerance = Peace."
(email, January 2018)


